WARNING: CHECK YoUR ORDERS BEFORE YOU LEAVE! I was pretty disappointed in this Taco Bell cantina. They need new management. When I came in those workers look MISERABLE! They got THREE things wrong in the order and I wish I would have opened all the food up and looked inside to make sure but who does that? They usually get the orders right in my neighborhood so why was this place lacking that so much. Another star off for the attitude that we got by the pick up station by the gentle man doing the orders. This was on a Friday night and close to 10:45pm. I felt even worse for delivery men because they were even more unprofessional to them. The employee at the pick up station was completely unhelpful and delivery men were left to fend for themselves. I only left two stars because they were opened and clean, social distance labels were in place neatly and the place was bright and had good music on. The other star was for the alcoholic drinks they made which were actually pretty tasty. I didn't have high hopes for another fast food restaurant in the area, but this was a Taco Bell Cantina! They surely have their stuff in order. Well... for the most part. It was my first time eating from there; and I ordered online and picked up (definitely a plus, since no other fast food restaurant in the neighborhood does that). I walked in, told them I was there for pickup (at the time I chose), and was given my food. I walked home and got ready to enjoy. That was until I realized they gave me what looked like two double decker tacos (no beans), instead of two loaded potato grillers. While I was bummed, I enjoyed the food nevertheless. The staff was friendly. The store was super clean. And the food was hot and fresh. This won't deter me from going there again, as there may have been an issue between the app and the store. But I have to give a fair review and deduct one star for failing to get the order correct the first time. I do recommend coming here though. For those adults in the area, come during dinner time when the teenagers are home (don't come after school, as you'll run into what looks like a packed store). Enjoy!
